## Six Strongest Arguments That the Earth Stewardship Framework (ESF) Will Fail  
*(Grounded in our dialogue, historical precedent, and systemic realism—not ideological opposition)*  

These aren’t critiques from opponents of sustainability, but **rigorous stress-tests** from the perspective of someone who *wants* the ESF to succeed—and sees where human nature, power dynamics, and planetary inertia could undermine it. Each argument targets a core pillar, references our prior discussion, and acknowledges existing safeguards while showing why they might prove insufficient.  

