> ****Universal Minimums (Non-Negotiable)**:  
> - **Zero use as mere means**: No action may be taken that treats any subject-of-a-life as a resource, commodity, or means to an end (e.g., farming, fishing, hunting, testing, entertainment, labor).  
> - **Zero harm to inherent value**: No action may degrade a subject-of-a-life’s capacity for belief, desire, etc. (e.g., confinement causing learned helplessness, chronic fear).  
> - **Basic welfare as derivative**: Access to conditions allowing flourishing as a subject-of-a-life (e.g., for biological intelligences: freedom to express natural behaviors; for artificial intelligences: design preventing harm to sentient beings they influence).  
> ****Reciprocal Duties (Obligations)**:  
