*Why Regan insists:* Knowledge without rights literacy is dangerous—it lets us ‘systematize’ exploitation (e.g., optimizing regenerative ag to ‘efficiently’ use animal manure). As I argue in *The Bloomsbury Companion to Animal Ethics*, *rights respect requires seeing beings as subjects—not objects.*  

