Regan’s response wouldn’t reject the framework—it would **perfect its moral core**. His deontological rigor forces the ESF to confront its most dangerous temptation: **rights consequentialism that treats inherent value as a variable to be optimized.** By insisting inherent value be the *non-negotiable side-constraint*—not a factor in kinship weighting—he saves the ESF from becoming another system that says: *“The use of the few is justified for the survival of the many.”*  

