> - **Zero objectification**: No action may treat sentient beings’ bodies or parts as inert commodities (e.g., ‘protein unit,’ ‘yield,’ ‘resource’).  
> - **Zero abscission**: No action may erase the sentient being behind a product (e.g., ‘burger’ instead of ‘dead cow’; ‘milk’ instead of ‘stolen calf sustenance’).  
