> *The absent referent isn’t ‘bad labeling’—it’s the system that makes exploitation *feel* inevitable by erasing the subject. Respecting kinship means dismantling the ideology that makes us *ignore* the individual behind the product.*  

*Why Adams insists*: This makes absent referent dismantlement *foundational*—not a variable. Boundary adherence isn’t the goal; it’s the *byproduct* of ending the mechanics that make exploitation feel normal. As I argue in *The Sexual Politics of Meat*, *patriarchy and speciesism thrive not in spite of knowledge—but by using knowledge to construct absence*.  

