> - Presence of fragmented language (e.g., ‘burger,’ ‘steak,’ ‘egg’) in messaging/policy  
> - Reliance on objectification (e.g., ‘protein unit,’ ‘yield,’ ‘resource’)  
> - Evidence of abscission (e.g., hiding the sentient being’s life story behind the product)  
