> - **Absent Referent Audits**: All governance/innovation processes must include an absent referent *impact audit* (not just assessment)—verifying no absent referent reinforcement in practice.  
> - **Absent Referent Drills**: Monthly practice of questioning absent referent assumptions (e.g., ‘Is this *really* necessary?’ or ‘Who benefits from calling this *normal*?’).  
> - **Whole-Being Language Training**: Teaching to center the sentient being (e.g., ‘This milk is stolen from a grieving mother’ not ‘This is dairy’).  
>  
> *Why Adams insists*: Knowledge without absent referent literacy is dangerous—it lets us ‘systematize’ exploitation while feeling virtuous (e.g., buying ‘cage-free’ eggs while ignoring chick culling happens *out of sight*). As I argue in *Never Too Late to Go Vegan*, *moral progress requires seeing through the absent referent—not just accumulating facts*.  

